          "description": "\u2b50\ufe0f\u2b50\ufe0f\u2b50\ufe0f\u2b50\ufe0f\u2b50\ufe0f\n\u201cA Royal Throne in the Concrete Jungle\u201d\n\nMove over Buckingham Palace, the true throne lies in Herald Square. I came in with fear in my heart and a grande iced coffee in my bladder, but what awaited me was nothing short of porcelain paradise.\n\nThe toilet paper? Two-ply luxury.\nThe flush? Powerful enough to erase your mistakes\u2014and possibly your sins.\nThe ambiance? Somewhere between \u201cairport chic\u201d and \u201curban survival,\u201d with a hint of eau de disinfectant that whispered, \u2018you\u2019re safe here, traveler.\u2019\n\nThere was even a hook on the stall door\u2014an underrated feature, really. My bag felt like it was staying at the Ritz.\n\n10/10 would poop here again.\nHerald Square Toilet: The Louvre of Loos, the Beyonc\u00e9 of Bathrooms. \ud83d\udca9\ud83d\udc51\ud83d\udebd",
